":"Flow Overview","markdown":"As the name suggests, this flow's purpose is to create a SAML app in Okta based on values passed from the parent flow 'SSO App Create'. \n\nThe first thing this flow does is determine if there are attributes to be processed. If there are, the Attribute Processing helper flow is called for each attribute. Once each needed attribute is processed, a series of nested object constructs are created in order to structure the body of the POST to Okta appropriately as each app could have a variety of different requirements.\n\nOnce the POST is sent to Okta and the application is created, ancillary actions such as group assignment and policy assignment are done via helper flows. This flow ends with a call back to ServiceNow, closing the associated RITM, and calling the Comms flow to provide relevant information to the app owner."}}},"pins":{}},{"joins":{},"address":"root:kernel:control:0.0.1:comment","parents":{"version":{"address":"root:kernel:control:0.0.1","key":"0.0.1","data":{"name":"0.0.1"}},"channel":{"address":"root:kernel:control","key":"control","data":{"name":"control"}}},"uuid":"4KSdjO2pI","branches":{},"node":{"key":"comment","data":{"name":"Comment"},"model":{"type":"method","_v":2,"key":"comment","executable":false,"displayed":true,"async":false,"cooperative":false,"mirrored":false,"inlined":false,"dependencies":[],"timeout":90000,"idempotent":false,"monitor":false,"webhook":false,"webhookList":false,"webhookConditions":false,"mobile":false,"hooks":{},"policy":{"error":{"type":"finish"}},"metadata":{"id":null,"name":"Comment","description":"Leave a comment."},"meta":{},"config":null,"partnerChannelKeys":null,"inputs":{"extensible":false,"data":{}},"outputs":{"extensible":false,"data":{}},"runtime":{},"display":{},"comments":{"title":"Okta Dashboard Visibility","markdown":"The SSO Form inside ServiceNow asks the submitter if the application supports IDP-initiated sign on. If yes, then the 'visibility' object will have its fields be set to allow it to appear."}}},"pins":{}},{"joins":{},"address":"root:kernel:control:0.0.1:comment","parents":{"version":{"address":"root:kernel:control:0.0.1","key":"0.0.1","data":{"name":"0.0.1"}},"channel":{"address":"root:kernel:control","key":"control","data":{"name":"control"}}},"uuid":"le3NPrAkn","branches":{},"node":{"key":"comment","data":{"name":"Comment"},"model":{"type":"method","_v":2,"key":"comment","executable":false,"displayed":true,"async":false,"cooperative":false,"mirrored":false,"inlined":false,"dependencies":[],"timeout":90000,"idempotent":false,"monitor":false,"webhook":false,"webhookList":false,"webhookConditions":false,"mobile":false,"hooks":{},"policy":{"error":{"type":"finish"}},"metadata":{"id":null,"name":"Comment","description":"Leave a comment."},"meta":{},"config":null,"partnerChannelKeys":null,"inputs":{"extensible":false,"data":{}},"outputs":{"extensible":false,"data":{}},"runtime":{},"display":{},"comments":{"title":"Okta Response Conditional","markdown":"If the application is created successfully in Okta, the app's row inside the App Create Table is updated to 'Pending Group Assign'. If it fails and the app is not created, a ServiceNow SCTask is opened under the RITM and the App Create Table updates the status to 'Error in App Create' while ending the flow."}}},"pins":{}},{"joins":{},"address":"root:kernel:control:0.0.1:comment","parents":{"version":{"address":"root:kernel:control:0.0.1","key":"0.0.1","data":{"name":"0.0.1"}},"channel":{"address":"root:kernel:control","key":"control","data":{"name":"control"}}},"uuid":"5i_2L2iyO","branches":{},"node":{"key":"comment","data":{"name":"Comment"},"model":{"type":"method","_v":2,"key":"comment","executable":false,"displayed":true,"async":false,"cooperative":false,"mirrored":false,"inlined":false,"dependencies":[],"timeout":90000,"idempotent":false,"monitor":false,"webhook":false,"webhookList":false,"webhookConditions":false,"mobile":false,"hooks":{},"policy":{"error":{"type":"finish"}},